{
    "name": "Vetala",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any (Vudra)<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary<br/><b>Treasure</b> NPC gear (chain shirt, <i>cloak of resistance +1</i>, <i>potions of invisibility </i>[2], other treasure)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "While most of the Inner Sea\u2019s vampires lust for living blood, the mysterious vetalas hunger for a more intangible force: the energy that infuses mortal minds. Referred to as consciousness or psyche by some, the academics of Vudra\u2014 from where most vetalas hail\u2014call this fundamental vital force prana. Regardless of their desire\u2019s name, vetalas prey upon those who show creative promise, possess potent force of will, or seem destined for greatness, draining the most brilliant sources of mortal light to fuel their own unnatural embers. Their dark mastery of life force allows vetalas to possess corpses or even overwhelm the minds of living creatures. With these stolen masks and the resources of abducted lives, they work their foul wills.<br/><br/>Vetalas are said to be the spirits of children \u201cborn evil,\u201d who never received burial rites upon their deaths. Sometimes one of these evil spirits takes hold of a corpse\u2014 not necessarily its own\u2014which becomes its anchor to the mortal world. Such young souls seek out experiences and life energy, becoming as wicked as any other vampire as they endlessly indulge their profane, deathless desires."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>With its bloodless flesh and eyes the color of deepest night, this imperious being obviously no longer numbers among the living.</i>",
